ns0:Concept.displayName: Single liveborn born in hospital by vaginal delivery (situation)

ns0:DescribedValueSet.ns0:Purpose: (Clinical Focus: This set of values contains types of delivery that represent the single live birth delivered vaginally.),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify patients who delivered a single live newborn vaginally. Using the Quality Data Model, this particular element will map to the "Diagnosis" category or the attribute of "Diagnoses" for Encounter category.),(Inclusion Criteria: Include codes that identify patients who delivered a single live newborn vaginally.),(Exclusion Criteria: Exclude codes that do not meet the inclusion criteria.)
